My wife loved the chops, and idk if I've had salmon this good anywhere else. And I LOVE salmon. Sides were also cooked to perfection. Drinks made great, and not too strong. And man, as far as the desserts, we had the bread pudding, and I'd put it up against any dessert from any restaurant. I'd Uber Eats just to have that delivered to wherever I am. A great, cozy, Black-owned business with tremendous food. Prices are a little on the high side, but it's very much in line for D.C.

Great live music and amazing food. OWNER IS A CROOK. Not honest with the advertising and pricing. Not organized with the reservations. Tried to force us to pay a 20% gratuity  First I'm going to start by saying I had an amazing evening (for the most part) with my wife for valentine's day at this place with great live music and amazing food.  Now, here's what I didn't like. I bought my tickets for the valentine's day event like 3 weeks in advance, with the assumption that I had reservations for a certain time and all costs were fully paid for. I arrive on time and when i get to the door and tell them i had reservations, they told me i had to wait 20+ minutes for a table to open up. No biggie. So we finally get a table and the waiter takes our order for appetizers. We wait... and wait... and wait. The table next to us sat down after we dis but got their appetizers and entree before we did. Turns out our waiter left and nobody replaced our table. Whatever. So we finally get our food and enjoy our evening.  Here's what really got me. We are getting ready to leave and the waitress brings us a bill. I inform her that I already paid in advance. She takes it back and brings back another bill saying that I owe a 20% gratuity plus 10% tax. First of all, sales tax in DC is only 6% and second, gratuity is an option and the amount is decided by the guest. So I talked to the manager and asked him why was I being charged a 20% gratuity and 10% tax if it wasn't mentioned in the ad when I made my advance purchase. He claimed it was mentioned. So we both looked at the ad and it only said "gratuity and tax not included." It didnt specify a certain amount. But like I said, gratuity is OPTIONAL and the amount is decided by the guest. You can't force someone to make an exceptional tip for average service. And sales tax should have been included in the initial purchase anyways. So we keep going back and forth and he insists that I owe the money that he claims.  I ended up leaving a tip (not the 20%) because our waitress did deserve one. But the manager/owner is a crook. Not sure if he handles business like that on a regular basis but we'll never return.  Thanks for reading.

A few weeks ago I made a reservation for my birthday, because I wanted to hear the live jazz band that played that night. I ordered a medium well steak and the one I received was well done. We notified the situation to the runner (she was next to us at the moment) and she apologized and picked up the plate. After several minutes the server arrived to ask me what happened and I explained. To my surprise, she dared to tell me that she was going to bring back the plate so that I could see that the steak in fact was medium well and not well done. I found this very rude: first, you are implying that I'm lying, and second you are implying that I do not know how a medium well steak looks or tastes like. She proceeded to bring the plate, and indeed that steak was medium well, but that was NOT my steak, because I cut it to double check the meat and my other four friends saw that it was well done. Why this server create such a scene? How did she have the nerve to bring it back from the kitchen? I do not know from whom that steak was but it was definitely not mine! I was so disappointed for the situation. I’ll never go back to that restaurant, the owner needs to provide her a customer service/hospitality workshop or something. Visiting D.C. from the West Coast for the first time. We made reservations to Jojo. First time visitor impressions and experience: cozy and intimate atmosphere, we were seated right away, friendly service, delicious and flavorful food with large portions, very short wait for food, and great music. Keep in mind that you'll need to make a reservation, entrance is down the stairs, the restaurant is two stories and the stage is on the bottom floor - you can't see the stage from the upper level. There is a monitor with live view of the stage on the upper level near the bar, it's in black and white and depending on where you're seated it may be difficult actually see the monitor clearly. Be sure to specify seating with stage view if you prefer that. You can still hear the music on the upper level but if there are a lot of guests it will distract from the music. This is a lively place with lots of conversation and laughter at all of the tables, very urban and just what I was looking for to get a feel of local fun as a tourist.
